<P>Cute problem -- one that forces me to question my usual assumptions.
I've also seen Mylar baloons made like this.  I'm not sure there is a
smooth surface formed by two squares sealed at the edges, containing a
nonzero volume, but of course you didn't say it had to be smooth.  You
can fill each of the four corners out into a circular cone, but then it
seems like you need some kind of crumpling in the middle of each square
to get it to match up with the cones, and I don't understand what that
part should look like.  Do you have a solution?
